This peptide arose from a Mycobacterium tuberculosis SHOTGUN database search for peptides containing a set of aminoacid requirements for stimulation of a T cell clone, defined as a way to validate the mimicry found between the original epitope of that clone (SPSMGRDIKVQFQS) and the mimotope recovered from a phage display 14-mer library (NSAIGIDIPVARRD). By that set of requirements(position 4 (P4) = (L,I,M,V,A,G,W,Y,F); P5= G; P6, (I,L,R,S,T,N,D,W,Y); P7=(D,N,S,T); P8= I; P9=(P,K,R,H); P10=(V,T,I,K)),  this peptide sequence was retrieved, and subsequently stated to be recognized by the T cell clone, validating the requirement definition and suggesting that similarity rather than homology is required for Ag recognition.

This peptide epitope was selected from a panel of 20mer overlapping peptides representing the entire length of the conserved hypothetical protein identified by an iterative genome screen of Mycobacterium bovis using StandAlone TBLASTIN (NCBI).
